[SN]TITLE[SN]
Dundee United's Cammy Ballantyne replaces Motherwell's Zack Jules for Scotland Under-21s

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Dundee United midfielder Cammy Ballantyne has been called up to the Scotland Under-21 squad ahead of Tuesday's match against Estonia.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
He replaces Zak Jules, the defender on loan at Motherwell from Reading who withdrew on Saturday.
Ballantyne becomes the 11th new face in Scot Gemmill's much-changed squad for the friendly at Paisley 2021 Stadium.
The 19-year-old has played 25 times this season on loan to League Two side Montrose, scoring once.
Ballantyne, who has previously been capped at under-17 level, has made two appearances for United, coming on as a substitute against Partick Thistle and Kilmarnock in the final two fixtures of last season.
